In an Event.REMOVED_FROM_STAGE listener, the stage should never be null, since you need that event to be able to remove event listeners from the stage. The following code can reproduce the issue. Just click the Quad.

```
package
{
    import starling.display.Quad;
    import starling.display.Sprite;
    import starling.events.Event;
    import starling.events.Touch;
    import starling.events.TouchEvent;
    import starling.events.TouchPhase;

    public class Main extends Sprite
    {
        public function Main()
        {
            var grandParent:Sprite = new Sprite();
            grandParent.addEventListener(Event.REMOVED_FROM_STAGE, grandParent_removedFromStageHandler);
            this.addChild(grandParent);
            var parent:Sprite = new Sprite();
            grandParent.addChild(parent);
            var child:Quad = new Quad(100, 100, 0xff00ff);
            child.addEventListener(Event.REMOVED_FROM_STAGE, child_removedFromStageHandler);
            child.addEventListener(TouchEvent.TOUCH, child_touchHandler);
            parent.addChild(child);
        }

        private function grandParent_removedFromStageHandler(event:Event):void
        {
            var grandParent:Sprite = Sprite(event.currentTarget);
            var parent:Sprite = Sprite(grandParent.getChildAt(0));
            parent.removeFromParent();
        }

        private function child_touchHandler(event:TouchEvent):void
        {
            var child:Quad = Quad(event.currentTarget);
            var touch:Touch = event.getTouch(child, TouchPhase.ENDED);
            if(!touch)
            {
                return;
            }

            var grandParent:Sprite = Sprite(child.parent.parent);
            grandParent.removeFromParent();
        }

        private function parent_removedFromStageHandler(event:Event):void
        {
            var parent:Quad = Quad(event.currentTarget);
            if(!parent.stage)
            {
                //this error won't be thrown
                throw new Error("Stage should not be null for parent!")
            }
        }

        private function child_removedFromStageHandler(event:Event):void
        {
            var child:Quad = Quad(event.currentTarget);
            if(!child.stage)
            {
                //this error will be thrown
                throw new Error("Stage should not be null for child!")
            }
        }
    }
}
```

In DisplayObject.as, the stage getter calls the base getter, which crawls up parent by parent until it reaches the stage:

```
public function get stage():Stage { return this.base as Stage; }

public function get base():DisplayObject
{
    var currentObject:DisplayObject = this;
    while (currentObject.mParent) currentObject = currentObject.mParent;
    return currentObject;
}
```

In DisplayObjectContainer.as, the removeChildAt() function broadcasts the Event.REMOVED_FROM_STAGE event. Then it sets the parent to null. If a child is removed in a Event.REMOVED_FROM_STAGE listener, it will rebroadcast the event and set the parent to null in that child before the original broadcast has completed. By the time it reaches grandchildren, their parent will have a null parent, so the stage  and base getters won't work.

```
        if (stage)
        {
            var container:DisplayObjectContainer = child as DisplayObjectContainer;
            if (container) container.broadcastEventWith(Event.REMOVED_FROM_STAGE);
            else           child.dispatchEventWith(Event.REMOVED_FROM_STAGE);
        }

        child.setParent(null);
```

