Just a heads up. I found a memory leak in the RenderTexture Class. Generally the rule is you should never use dynamic function calls as they eat up memory and have to each be dynamically created.

Now personally i thought that this had been updated in recent versions of flash but apparently it has not.

Reproduction use drawBundled() function to draw a couple hundred objects to the world. (I've also seen it occur with even 5 objects though hundred is more apparent) now watch your memory climb.

The reason this is such a big problem is b/c every time the system on both pc and mobile clears away the junk memory the frames drop drastically. (on 30 fps game drops to 24) now that stutter ruins the entire gameplay.

Why i want you guys to fix this is b/c i like using the vanilla starling i don't want to have to make any changes to the engine and i want to be able to get the latest build without having to worry about custom code so it would appreciated if you fix this.

Problem Code:

<pre lang="as3">
public function draw(object:DisplayObject, matrix:Matrix=null, alpha:Number=1.0,
                             antiAliasing:int=0):void
        {
            if (object == null) return;

            if (mDrawing)
                render();
            else
                drawBundled(render, antiAliasing);

            function render():void
            {
                mSupport.loadIdentity();
                mSupport.blendMode = object.blendMode;

                if (matrix) mSupport.prependMatrix(matrix);
                else        mSupport.transformMatrix(object);

                object.render(mSupport, alpha);
            }
        }
</pre>

My Fix:

