public function draw(object:DisplayObject, matrix:Matrix=null, alpha:Number=1.0,
                             antiAliasing:int=0):void
        {
            if (object == null) return;

            if (mDrawing)
                render(object,matrix,alpha,antiAliasing);
            //else
                //drawBundled(render, antiAliasing);

        }
        //Fixed Memory Leak
private function render(object:DisplayObject, matrix:Matrix=null, alpha:Number=1.0,
                             antiAliasing:int=0):void
        {
            mSupport.loadIdentity();
            mSupport.blendMode = object.blendMode;

            if (matrix) mSupport.prependMatrix(matrix);
            else        mSupport.transformMatrix(object);

            object.render(mSupport, alpha);
        }
</pre>

Now i know this only works for batch drawing the only way i could theoretically see around it is separate render calls for the non-batched draw should cache store vars temporarily and then use them in separate function call. Clear the cache at the end of the drawBatch Call if there is one...

Feedback is always welcome.
